5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 631, L.D. 971, “An Act to Repeal the
10 Law Regarding Checking Baitfish Traps”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Amend the Law Regarding the Checking of Baitfish Traps'
13 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
14 following:
15 'Sec. 1. 12 MRSA §12555, sub-§1, as enacted by PL 2003, c. 655, Pt. B, §265 and
16 affected by §422, is amended to read:
17 1. Prohibition Checking baitfish traps. While trapping for baitfish in the inland
18 waters with the use of a baitfish trap as defined in section 10001, subsection 7 from April
19 2nd to October 31st, a person shall check the baitfish trap or cause the baitfish trap to be
20 checked at least once in every 7 calendar days. While trapping for baitfish in the inland
21 waters with the use of a baitfish trap from November 1st to April 1st, a person shall check
22 the baitfish trap or cause the baitfish trap to be checked at least once in every 21 calendar
23 days.
24 Sec. 2. Report. The Department of Inland Fisheries and Wildlife shall submit a
25 report related to the baitfish trap checking requirements under the Maine Revised Statutes,
26 Title 12, section 12555, subsection 1 to the joint standing committee of the Legislature
27 having jurisdiction over inland fisheries and wildlife matters by January 1, 2029. The report
28 must include information on whether increasing the time permitted between baitfish trap
29 checks from November 1st to April 1st has led to any biological consequences or
30 enforcement challenges. The report must also include information on reported complaints
31 and accidents, if any, and may include recommendations for suggested legislation. The
32 committee may report out a bill based on the report to the 134th Legislature in 2029.'
33 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
34 number to read consecutively.
